title: Data from the General Social Survey (GSS) from the National Opinion Research Center of the University of Chicago.
description:
Description
This data set illustrates analyis of a multifactor observational study, with response given by subject's score on a vocabulary test, and factors for age group, education level, natality status, gender and year of the survey.
reference: This file includes the years of the GSS for which the vocab and nativeBorn items were included.

parameters.age: age of the respondent in years
parameters.gender: a factor with levels female male
parameters.year: a factor with levels 1978 1982 1984 1987 1988 1989 1990 1991 1993 1994 1996 1998 2000 2004 2006 2008 2010 2012 2014 2016.  Data are included from the GSS for each of these years.
parameters.nativeBorn: Was the respondent born in the US?  A factor with levels no and yes.
parameters.educGroup: a factor with levels <12 yrs 12 yrs 13-15 yrs 16 yrs >16 yrs, grouped education level of the respondent.  12 years corresponds to high school graduate, 16 years to college graduate.
parameters.vocab: Number of words out of 10 correct on a vocabulary test
parameters.educ: years of education of the respondent
parameters.ageGroup: a factor with levels 18-29 30-39 40-49 50-59 60+, grouped age of the respondent.

format: A data frame with 28867 observations on the following 8 variables.
